ider id/name), the model row the model string. A broken binding raises terminal `TaskFailed(AUTH_ERROR)`; write-time referential checks return `AGENT_RUNNER_CONFIG_INVALID` → 422; `GET /api/runner/status` reports bindings and binary probes. Resolution per run means agent edits and key rotations apply without restarts — nothing caches a built runner.\n \n-Subprocesses are blocking, hopped off the event loop via `asyncio.to_thread`; runners know **nothing** about retries or ordering — they are a pure \"execute this task now\" hand. The execution handler passes `plan:goal:task:run:number:attempt` as the additive idempotency key. CLI runners preserve legacy three-part keys and, for the canonical form, inject only `ORCHESTRATOR_PLAN_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_GOAL_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_TASK_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_RUN_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_ATTEMPT_NUMBER`, and `ORCHESTRATOR_ATTEMPT_ID` into the child environment. The task prompt is a markdown contract (`build_task_prompt`); project conventions belong in the workspace's `AGENTS.md`, not in the runner.\n+Subprocesses are managed through the shared `supervise_process()` supervisor,\n+which reads stdout and stderr incrementally rather than using one blocking\n+`communicate()` call; the supervisor's timeout and process-group termination/\n+reaping behavior remains in force. The synchronous subprocess work is still\n+hopped off the event loop via `asyncio.to_thread`; runners know **nothing** about\n+retries or ordering — they are a pure \"execute this task now\" hand. The\n+execution handler passes `plan:goal:task:run:number:attempt` as the additive\n+idempotency key. CLI runners preserve legacy three-part keys and, for the\n+canonical form, inject only `ORCHESTRATOR_PLAN_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_GOAL_ID`,\n+`ORCHESTRATOR_TASK_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_RUN_ID`, `ORCHESTRATOR_ATTEMPT_NUMBER`,\n+and `ORCHESTRATOR_ATTEMPT_ID` into the child environment. The task prompt is a\n+markdown contract (`build_task_prompt`); project conventions belong in the\n+workspace's `AGENTS.md`, not in the runner.\n \n ## The workspace — git branching as the rollback mechanism\n \n M docs/architecture/events-and-observability.md\n M docs/architecture/execution-model.md\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Updated only:\n\n- `docs/architecture/events-and-observability.md`\n  - Added the CLI supervisor/log-file paragraph.\n  - Added the attempt-log endpoint to the operator visibility table.\n\n- `docs/architecture/execution-model.md`\n  - Updated the CLI subprocess paragraph to document incremental streaming, `supervise_process()`, and preserved timeout/process-group cleanup.\n\nNo changes to `ROADMAP.md`, `known-issues.md`, or Python files. `git diff --check` passed.\n\nNew observability paragraph:\n\n> CLI runners read subprocess stdout and stderr incrementally through the shared `supervise_process()` supervisor. For attempts with a canonical `attempt_id`, the supervisor writes bounded JSONL records to `$ORCHESTRATOR_HOME/runtime-logs/<attempt_id>.jsonl` via `attempt_log_path()`; its process observations contain lifecycle metadata such as byte counts, exit code, duration, and log path, never raw output.\n\nNew execution-model paragraph:\n\n> Subprocesses are managed through the shared `supervise_process()` supervisor, which reads stdout and stderr incrementally rather than using one blocking `communicate()` call; the supervisor's timeout and process-group termination/reaping behavior remains in force. The synchronous subprocess work is still hopped off the event loop via `asyncio.to_thread`; runners know **nothing** about retries or ordering — they are a pure \"execute this task now\" hand."}}
